<title type="html"><![CDATA[Classic Shell - NORTON - Virus - False Positive.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2434&amp;p=11927#p11927"><![CDATA[
Hello All.<br /><br />A review and nothing more.<br /><br />Recently I had to upgrade to Windows 7 from XP (I liked XP <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> It did everything I needed. But MS is removing support, so I was forced to move house. <br /><br />That's where my issues really began.<br /><br />The W7 file-manager is really screwed up. It's minimalist to a point that it's unusable, and the lack of 'tree-lines' in the file panel : was really, really annoying me. Amongst other things.<br /><br />Started digging on Goggle, and found something called Classic Shell.<br /><br />Downloaded the installer : NORTON refused to allow me to run the programme for Classic shell (4.0.6) <br />- And insisted it was identified as a crowd style mal-ware programme.<br /><br /><strong>  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" />  </strong><strong>IT IS NOT.</strong> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <br /><br />But to run the programme, and tell NORTON to 'restore' the file: <br />- You have top be logged in as an <strong>Administrator.</strong> <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_idea.gif" alt=":idea:" title="Idea" /> <br /><br />I run my system as a <strong>'Guest'.</strong>  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_question.gif" alt=":?:" title="Question" /> <br /><br />After you have done all that, and finally run the file 'ClassicShellSetup_4_0_6.exe' as an Admin - you are presented with an extra set of options on your menu bar. As in:<br /><br />'menu1'<br /><br />Click on the 'shell'  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_exclaim.gif" alt=":!:" title="Exclamation" /> and then : Play-Away: <br />All I can say from running, and playing with the options is : ** Wow ** - <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" />  What a programme. <br />Finally something that makes Windows actually useful, and productive again. <br /><br />And as a bonus : I've finally got my folder tree lines back. As in:<br /><br />'tree-view'<br /><br />Donated to it, and would advise others to do the same, but if you feel that $10.00 is too much, then donate 5.00 - Give the guy something for his hard work! - This programme is the bees-knees.<br />It's very good, and I cannot recommend it enough.<br /><br />RGDS - Terry - SWN:  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3414">tusk.1951</a> — Sun Apr 06, 2014 2:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
